title: Japanese White Sweet Potato And Sole With Zucchini, Cauliflower
summary: The recipe Japanese White Sweet Potato And Sole With Zucchini, Cauliflower could satisfy your Japanese craving in roughly 45 minutes. This recipe serves 2. One serving contains 431 calories, 9g of protein, and 29g of fat. For $2.77 per serving, this recipe covers 19% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe from La Tartine Gourmande has 46 fans. It is a good option if you're following a gluten free, dairy free, whole 30, and pescatarian diet. A mixture of japanese sweet potato, japanese sweet potato and sole, japanese sweet potato, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so scrumptious. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 83%. This score is awesome. Try Japanese Soy Glazed Sweet Potato, Japanese Chestnut And Sweet Potato Soup, and Japanese Sweet Potato with Honey Butter for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Gewurztraminer, Chenin Blanc, and Riesling are great choices for Asian. The best wine for Asian food depends on the cuisine and dish - of course - but these acidic whites pair with a number of traditional meals, spicy or not. The Cave de Ribeauville Collection Gewurztraminer with a 4.5 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 19 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Cave de Ribeauville Collection Gewurztraminer
productMatches.description: This lemon yellow wine has an intensely aromatic bouquet, with notes of spice and lychee. On the palate, the mature acidity keeps the wine fresh, yet finessed. Pair with spicy food, soft cheeses, and pastries.Gewurztraminer is the most aromatic of Alsace wines. With its aromas of rose, lychee and spices, it embellishes our palate. Soft, it goes well with foie gras, a fruit-based dessert. Semi-dry, it accompanies spicy dishes or strong cheeses.
